# Cloudflare Pages routing — R1 (ADR 0040): marketing landing at /, editor SPA at /app.
#
# Cloudflare Pages "clean URLs" are always on: it serves app.html at /app and
# 308-redirects /app.html -> /app. So we must NOT rewrite to a *.html destination
# here — a `/app -> /app.html 200` rewrite collides with that clean-URL redirect
# and loops forever (ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS). Real files (/, /privacy, /site.css,
# /static/*, …) are served directly and take precedence over these rules.

# Preserve legacy share links minted before R1: /display/… -> /app/display/…
/display/*   /app/display/:splat   301

# SPA deep-route fallback (hard refresh on /app/<client-route>, e.g. share links).
# Rewrite to the CLEAN /app (Pages serves app.html there natively) — never
# /app.html, which would clean-URL-redirect back to /app and loop. 200 = rewrite,
# so the deep path stays in the address bar for React Router to read. The bare
# /app needs no rule: Pages serves app.html at /app via clean URLs.
/app/*       /app                  200

# Anything else that is not a real file is a genuine 404 (not the landing).
/*           /404.html             404
